node.text: I made a video of how I told Cole  and our friends & family that I was pregnant! I found out in the morning before when we were getting ready for the beach and totally thought the test was going to be negative. I was shocked when it said positive and had Knox run the test out to Cole! I still can’t believe our little family is growing ✨

node.title: So much love for this little babe already👶🏼💛

node.text: Watching you become a dad has been my most favorite thing. Fatherhood comes to effortlessly and naturally to you and it’s really amazing to see you in action. You are nurturing, playful, loving, selfless and all in. I could not ask for a better husband and daddy to my future babies.

node.title: Happy Fathers Day to the best dad 💙

These are pantry friendly, kid friendly, refined sugar/ flour free and DELICIOUS! I came up with this recipe a few weeks ago when I needed something to keep us all full on a 10 hour flight. Knox loves them and even got his first little taste of chocolate yesterday because I forgot to to make few without chocolate chips 🙈 Make extra and bring them to family/ friends to let them know you’re thinking of them 💛 Save this post for future reference & share it with a friend! I want to make more recipe videos and next time I’m thinking a dinner meal! Comment what recipes you want to see below 👇🏽 ⁣
*Makes 12 Muffins* ⁣
Ingredients:⁣
- 2 cups oat flour ⁣
- 2 eggs⁣
- 1/3 cup coconut oil ⁣
- 1/3 cup pure maple syrup (or honey) ⁣
- 1 cup mashed bananas⁣
- 1/4 cup milk ( I use almond or oat milk)⁣
- 1 tsp. baking soda⁣
- 1 tsp. Vanilla ⁣
- 1/2 tsp. Sea salt ⁣
- 1 tsp. cinnamon ⁣
- 1/3 cup chopped pecans ⁣
-1/4 cup chocolate chips ⁣
⁣
Directions: ⁣
- Preheat the oven to 325 (162 Celsius)⁣
- Scoop 2 cups of organic oats into a blender. Blend until it is the consistency of flour ⁣
- Mix together all of the ingredients and pour the batter into a greased muffin tin.⁣
- Bake for 20-22 minutes and enjoy!⁣
⁣
Xo, Maddie 
Sound: Bound 2 Instrumental

node.text:
The perfect blend of sweet, tangy and delicious🌟 My neighbor brought over some fresh lilikoi from her tree and I threw this together! If ya wanna try it out here’s the recipe:
•4 lilikoi (seeds included) • 1 frozen banana (I ran out of frozen ones but it will make the smoothie thicker)
• 1 cup of frozen mango
• 1 cup of frozen peach •1 cup of frozen strawberry • splash of nut milk 
Top with homemade granola, fresh strawberries, banana, more lilikoi, coconut or whatever you’d like! 🍓🥥
We’re also got the product samples in for our shop launching in the New Year 🙌🏽 Any guesses what products from the video we might be releasing?! I am blown away by how this community has grown over the years! This all started while I was a college student trying to create a healthier lifestyle for myself. I never could’ve dreamed I would get the opportunity to connect with all of you from around the world! THANK YOU! I’ll be sending my smoothie ebook to a few of you who comment 💛

node.text: I’m showing you what our typical grocery haul looks like each month! This is definitely one of our biggest because we hadn’t gone grocery shopping in over a month. We live an hour away from the nearest big super market so we typically do one big trip a month and then buy fruits and veggies from our local store in between trips 🥑🍉🍓🍍🍌#summerofwellness

node.text: The story of the day our little angel came into the the world 💙

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maddie Castellano on September 10, 2021 tagging @austinrichmond, and @cole_castellano. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and ocean.

node.text: Story time: When Cole and I were dating I kept thinking that he was going to propose. There was one day that I was absolutely certain it was going to happen. My parents were in town, he had just asked for my dads permission and we were going to watch the sunset at “our spot”. Everyone started getting in the car and I had the realization that possibly going to happen that night. I said I had to go to the bathroom real quick and I sprinted inside and painted just my left hand in record speed 💅🏼 He ended up not proposing for another week because he had to wait for his tax return to come so he could afford a ring 🥲 but at least my left hand was prepared haha

node.text: This is the picture Knox will show when people ask “what do your parents look like?” 🥺🤍

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maddie Castellano on September 03, 2021 tagging @cole_castellano. May be an image of 3 people, baby, people standing and outdoors.

node.text: My favorite view 😍 I am still tripping that both my babies have blonde hair! I had dark, dark hair as a baby, but Cole was a blondie until he was 12. I’m so curious if they’ll stay tow heads or if it’ll get darker the older they get!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maddie Castellano on September 02, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, baby and people standing.

node.text: Enzo boy is 7 months old today! This stage has been ohhh so sweet.  I want to freeze time for a moment and just soak up all his chunky cuteness. He really is the happiest baby and rarely fusses or cries! His resting face is a smile and he loves to squak and giggle. This month he started sitting up and he’s now learning how to crawl! He’s so active that changing his diaper feels like wrestling an alligator 😂 Life wouldn’t be the same with our you Zo. I love this nugget so much it hurts.

node.text: Growing up when I would imagine my future, I never pictured myself as a boy mom! I have two sisters and one brother so I always thought I’d have mostly girls. To be honest, I was shocked at both gender reveals when I saw the blue! I was so sure Knox was going to he a girl I even went and bought some baby girl clothes 😂 Now, I truly can’t picture life going any other way! These two boys are as sweet as they come. I feel so lucky to he their mama 💛

node.text: Fun date night idea! ✨ Over the weekend Cole and I went back to the spot where we got engaged and had a “water picnic” in the ocean! We grabbed our surf boards, got sushi takeout and floated out to sea while we laughed and ate. We got this idea from @theadventurechallenge book with tons of surprise dates that are planned for you! You could totally do this same date on the lake, river or even the pool! We’ve gotten stuck in the same rut of date ideas and it was SO fun to get creative and mix it up. How the book works,  is it labels everything you need to know before going.  It tells you if you need a babysitter, what time of day, how much money, how long, etc. , but the date is kept a total surprise! You scratch it off when you’re ready to go and then you have a fun and unique date already planned for you. I’m already looking forward to our next one! You can use the code MADDIE for 20% off 🤍 What’s the best date you’ve ever been on? 🥰

node.text: Enzo hitting us with that smolder, are you kidding me? 🤩 Even though he’s 7 months old now, I'm still working to feel “normal” again. Before having kids, I always thought the postpartum period lasted a few months, but personally it’s taken me around a year to feel back to myself! Recently, I started taking @ritual essential protein for pregnancy & postpartum and I love it! Mornings are always a little hectic around here and my protein smoothies help me feel full through it! I love that Ritual is made with clean, traceable ingredients and no added sugars! It also contains all 9 essential amino acids making it a complete protein source. If you want to try Ritual, use my code MADDIE3 for 10% off your first 3 months ✨ #ritualpartner

node.text: This morning I said “I love you Knox!” And he responded with “I know. I love you too mama” 🥺 Any hard motherhood moment was worth it all just to hear that. What’s something that made you smile today? ✨

node.text: 6 months out vs. 9 months in 🤍 These photos were taken the day before I went into labor with Enzo! I remember being in so much pain from 3 weeks of prodromal labor, but I’m so glad we took them because they are some of the last pictures with my bump! Looking back at these is making me realize how fast Knox is growing up too 🥺 Maternity pics taken by @emmaericksonmcc ✨
